Creative Feature
Animated Skill Bars
The skill bars use the Intersection Observer API to detect when the skills section enters the viewport. When this happens, each bar smoothly animates from zero percent to its target value using CSS transitions. The percentage numbers also animate using requestAnimationFrame so they count up smoothly instead of jumping to the final value.
This feature makes the page more engaging and demonstrates my ability to build interactive behavior without relying on any external libraries.

6. Conclusion
This personal homepage serves both as a portfolio and as a learning exercise. It shows that I can build a responsive and accessible website using modern web standards without relying on frameworks. The content reflects my real experience and career goals, making it a practical tool for job searching and networking.
The design focuses on clarity and usability rather than flashy visuals. The animated skill bars and interactive project cards add just enough personality to make the site memorable. Most importantly, this is a site I feel comfortable sharing because it represents who I am as a developer and what I am working toward.

